http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/App-to-download-%E2%80%98Sri-Siddhanta-Shikhamani%E2%80%99/article13979951.ece

‘Sri Siddhanta Shikhamani App’, a mobile application that helps download ‘Sri Siddhanta Shikhamani’, a religious text of Veerashavism in 16 different languages, will be released at a function in Bengaluru on January 5.Kashi Jnana Peetha seer Chandrashekhara Shivacharya Bhagavatpada told presspersons here on Sunday that the peetha had developed this application to target youngsters who prefer to have information on their finger tips.“While this application will help extend the tenets of Veerashaivism to a larger section of the people, the public too could have an easy access to it,” he said.LanguagesIt will be available in Sanskrit, Kannada, Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, Marathi, Hindi, Avadhi, Maithili, Bhojpuri, Odiya, Gujarati, English, Russian and Nepali languages.The Bengali and Urdu version would be made available soon.While the seer himself translated the text into Kannada, 16 scholars of different languages have translated the other versions.Indian Space Research Organisation chairman A.S. Kiran Kumar would release the app at a function at Sri basaveshwars Sujnana Mantapa located at Vijayanagar in Bengaluru.FunctionThe former Chief Minister B.S. Yeddyurappa would preside over the function. Seers Srimalaya Shantamuni Shivacharya of Shivaganga, Mahantalinga Shivacharya of Vibhutimath, Bengaluru, and the former minister V. Somanna would also be present.‘It will help extend the tenets of Veerashaivism toa larger section of people’